#  Networking Fundamentals

##  Overview
This section covers the foundational concepts of networking used in cybersecurity.

##  What I Learned

- OSI Model & TCP/IP basics
- Common network protocols (HTTP, DNS, TCP, UDP)
- Difference between secure and insecure protocols
- Packet structure and communication flow

##  Tools Used

### Wireshark
- Captured and analyzed network traffic
- Identified protocols and packet behavior

### tcpdump
- Basic command-line packet capture
- Filtering traffic

### Nmap
- Network scanning and host discovery
- Port scanning and service detection

##  Key Takeaways

- Understanding network traffic is essential for both attack and defense
- Enumeration is the first step in any penetration test
- Protocol knowledge helps identify vulnerabilities
